<div id="review_2979786786" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2979786786" />
    <a title="Ian" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/31384949-ian"><img alt="Ian" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1623178551p2/31384949.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2979786786?book_show_action=true">Sep 29, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ian" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ian" href="/user/show/31384949-ian">Ian</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/11546057-the-leopard">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/31384949-ian?shelf=4-star-lit-fiction">4-star-lit-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/31384949-ian?shelf=italy">italy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/31384949-ian?shelf=modern-classics">modern-classics</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/31384949-ian?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2979786786" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer850070684575716622">Although this is a very famous novel I’d not personally heard of it until I joined GR in 2014. Over the past 5 years I’ve seen various reviews of it, always positive, and so was persuaded to try it.<br/><br/>As is well-known, the bulk of the novel is set in Sicily in the 1860s. The central character, Prince Fabrizio Salina, exercises a paternalistic rule over the tenants of his vast estates, across a Sicily that seems timeless but which is now faced with change, or, as the Prince views it, with decay. The</span>
  <span id="freeText850070684575716622" style="display:none">Although this is a very famous novel I’d not personally heard of it until I joined GR in 2014. Over the past 5 years I’ve seen various reviews of it, always positive, and so was persuaded to try it.<br /><br />As is well-known, the bulk of the novel is set in Sicily in the 1860s. The central character, Prince Fabrizio Salina, exercises a paternalistic rule over the tenants of his vast estates, across a Sicily that seems timeless but which is now faced with change, or, as the Prince views it, with decay. The combination of Italian unification and the rise of a new commercial class threatens to overwhelm the traditional political and economic roles of the island’s ossified aristocracy, and the Prince realises that his family will have to adapt to the changes. A subplot featuring the Salina family priest, Father Pirrone, provides the reader with an insight into Sicilian peasant society. <br /><br />I could only read the English translation, but it seems a high quality one, conveying a fine sense of the richness of the writing. It says much for the author’s skill that he makes a feudal aristocrat like Don Fabrizio such a sympathetic figure to the modern reader. For me, the dominant theme of the novel is one of sadness, one might say hopelessness. <br /><br />Over the last couple of weeks I’ve not had as much time for reading as I would have liked. This rather broke up my enjoyment of the book. It’s one I might return to one day.<br /><br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="850070684575716622" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


